kpi_info.title: period_duration

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_NOF_CIRCUITS

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_NOF_WOEX_CRTS_IN

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_NOF_WOEX_CRTS_OUT

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_TIMECONG_PERCENTx100
kpi_info.use: Time congestion percentage (0.0...100.0)in the circuit group in relation to the results accumulation period.Principle of time congestion (TC) calculation:Time congestion in a circuit group is calculated in relation to the results accumulation period.Time congestion is calculated when all time slots available on the circuit group are in use, or the state of circuits prevents their use for outgoing traffic. Calculating time congestion is stopped when there are again time slots available (one or more calls are released, circuits are added, or the state of the circuit changes so that it becomes available for outgoing traffic).The field is only used for outgoing (OUT) circuit groups (including the OUT circuits in bidirectional circuit groups) (0.0...100.0%).The field is empty if the value is not available.

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_CALL_CONG_x_100
kpi_info.use: Number of call attempts (0...65535) terminatedin call congestion.A call attempt terminates in call congestion if all the available circuits have already been reserved, or if the Automatic Congestion Control (ACC) or Selective Circuit Reservation (SCR) features are used to limit the traffic. Call Congestion counter is updated for all circuit groups where circuit reservation attempt leads to congestion. This is done even if alternative routes have been defined (this means that the call setup continues on an alternative route).Call congestion is updated of all known congested calls. That includes mobile originating calls (BSC circuit groups) and originating calls from PBX types for which the MSC takes care of the hunting of free circuits. The total congestion in circuit group measurement is measured and reported as outgoing congestion (OUT) because the direction of congestion is not available.The field is empty if the value is not available.Note: The column name is misleading for historical reasons. Despite the column name there is no multiplication by 100 contained in this counter.

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_CALL_AMOUNT_IN

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_CALL_AMOUNT_OUT

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_EXT_FAIL_OUT

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_ERLANGS_IN_x_100
kpi_info.use: The amount of traffic on the circuit groupin erlangs (0.0...9999.9). That means the total reservation time of the object being measured in relation to the results accumulation period.The Erlangs are calculated from circuit seizure to circuit release.All of the circuit reservation time is updated in the results accumulation period in which the circuit is released. For this reason, remarkably large values in the ERLANGS field are possible in a case in which there are many calls that have started before the results accumulation period but that end in the results accumulation period. In such a case, the value in the ERLANGS field can be greater than the value of the fields CRTS and AVECR.

kpi_info.use: The amount of traffic on the circuit groupin erlangs (0.0...9999.9). For this reason, remarkably large values in the ERLANGS field are possible in a case in which there are many calls that have started before the results accumulation period but that end in the results accumulation period. In such a case, the value in the ERLANGS field can be greater than the value of the fields CRTS and AVECR.

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_INVALID_RECORD

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_CORRUPT_MESSAGE

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_DATA_PROV_RESTARTED

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_SUCC_TRAFF_IN_X100
kpi_info.use: The successful call duration. The measured object is the incoming traffic on the given circuit group. The possible values range from 0.0 to 999999.9, and they are given in ERLANGS. It is updated at the end of the call, which means that the MSC Server has received the CC-Relelase Complete or ISUP/BICC Release Complete message. The Successful traffic is the cumulative time between the Alerting / ACM and Release complete message. The value of tha counter is 100 x the incoming successful traffic.

kpi_info.title: CGRCGROUP_ANSW_TRAFF_IN_X100
kpi_info.use: The answered call duration. The measured object is the incoming traffic on the given circuit group. The possible values range from 0.0 to 999999.9, and they are given in ERLANGS. It is updated at the end of the call, which means that the MSC Server has received the CC-Relelase Complete or ISUP/BICC Release Complete message. The Successful traffic is the cumulative time between the CONNECT ACK / Answer and the Release Complete message. The value of the counter is 100 x the incoming successful traffic.
